cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY 

The paper discusses a neural network architecture for multisensory integration and recalibration, which involves features of the dorsal processing hierarchy and top-down feedback connections. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.NE is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a neural network architecture. The other categories are also likely as the paper involves topics such as computer vision, machine learning, and control systems.
